THE Durban High Court has on Thursday, 26 May, convicted and sentenced two accused to life in jail for the murder of reservist Constable Malusi Mahlangu, who was fatally shot at kwaNdengezi. Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said Mahlangu was on duty at Mariannhill satellite station when he was approached by the complainant, whose tuck shop had been robbed. “He proceeded to the shop and upon arrival, he was shot at and robbed of the state firearm. He was taken to hospital for medical attention, where he was declared dead on arrival,” Mhlongo said in a statement. He added that a case of murder was reported at KwaNdengezi Police Station, and then allocated to the Hawks. Mnqobi Mdluli (29) and Siphosihle Philant (34) were arrested and charged with murder as well as two counts of robbery. “They were further sentenced to 30 years for the robberies, of which would run concurrently,” he added.